    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-10T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-10T08:00:00-05:00" n="712"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.8131/66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-10T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 10, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1112. Your 789, December 2, 10 p.m. It now appears that I shall be able to
                    proceed by air from Vichy directly to North Africa. This will afford a
                    considerable saving of time. I will notify the Department of the date of
                    departure.</p>
                <p>I am requesting Lisbon to endeavor to convey the memorandum in question to me
                    here or at Casablanca, but as this might not prove practicable I should be
                    grateful if the Department would telegraph the gist of the memorandum to me
                    here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
